name: ExtensionMedicinalProductDefinition_Operation
title: Cross-version Extension `R5.MedicinalProductDefinition.operation` for use in FHIR R4
description: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element `MedicinalProductDefinition.operation` for use in FHIR R4.
purpose:
This extension is part of the cross-version definitions generated to enable use of the
element `MedicinalProductDefinition.operation` as defined in FHIR R5
in FHIR R4.

The source element is defined as:
`MedicinalProductDefinition.operation` 0..* `BackboneElement`

Across FHIR versions, the element set has been mapped as:
*  R5: `MedicinalProductDefinition.operation` 0..* `BackboneElement`
*  R4B: `MedicinalProductDefinition.operation` 0..* `BackboneElement`

Following are the generation technical comments:
Element `MedicinalProductDefinition.operation` is will have a context of MedicinalProduct based on following the parent source element upwards and mapping to `MedicinalProduct`.

element.definition: A manufacturing or administrative process or step associated with (or performed on) the medicinal product.
